meta {
  name: 07 Create Response (streaming) (openclaw)
  type: http
  seq: 7
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/v1/responses
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "input": "Count from 1 to 5, one number per line.",
    "agent": "openclaw",
    "reasoning_effort": "low",
    "stream": true
  }
}

docs {
  Streaming is agent-agnostic: pass `"agent": "openclaw"` alongside
  `"stream": true` and the gateway streams the OpenClaw turn back as Server-Sent
  Events, exactly like the Hermes streaming request above:
    response.created -> response.reasoning.delta / response.output_text.delta /
    response.tool_call.* -> response.completed (or response.failed)

  The OpenClaw adapter requests `stream: true` from OpenClaw's own
  `/v1/responses` and re-streams its SSE, so there's no extra setup beyond a
  local OpenClaw:
    openclaw start   (listens on http://localhost:18789)

  Bruno shows the assembled event stream in the Response pane. For raw frames:

    curl -N localhost:3737/v1/responses \
      -H 'content-type: application/json' \
      -d '{"input":"hi","agent":"openclaw","stream":true}'
}
